                <td align="left" style="padding:5 10" width="388"><font class="title01">Korean firm pursues Thai CDMA market</font> </td>
				<td valign="bottom"><img src="/english/images/bbs_line.gif"></td>
                <td width="100" align="center">Sep.18,2003</td>
              </tr>
			  <tr class="bbs05"> 
                <td height="1" colspan="5"><img src="/english/images/blank.gif"></td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bbs03"> 
                <td colspan="2" height="21" align="center">&nbsp;</td>
                <td colspan="3" align="left" style="padding:5 10">Pantech&Curitel, Korea's third largest mobile phone maker, plans<br>
to market it's CDMA handset brand in Thailand by the end of the year as part of its policy to expand in the fast-growing Southeast Asian region.<br>
 Heavily based on CDMA technology manufactured under the Curitel brand.<br>
the former subsidiary of hyundai raised US$100 million yesterday by listing on<br>
the Korean stock market.<br>
<br>
 Senior voice-president S.G kang said the company would use the proceeds to expand<br>
business overseas, develop technology and improve research and development of new handset products.<br>
"We are working closely with our local business partner(Hutchison) to set up our own brand office in Thailand within this year, with business activity set to begin next month." he said.<br>
 Curiel currently has branch offices in Taiwan, Indonesia and Vietnam.<br>
<br>
 "Given the population factor and high mobile penetration rate and great business" Potential in the Thai CDMA-technology market following the debut of the Hutch system locally, we are confident our brand would easily get good recognition and achieve success in Thailand," Mr. Kang said.<br>
<br>
 He said the company initially planned to offer cost-competitive initially planned to offer cost-competitive handset with a variety of functions and features and database applications, targeting the fast-growing youth market in Thailand.<br>
"We expect to sell up to one million phones in Thailand." he said without giving a timeframe.<br>
"Business success in Thailand will be the key driving force for us to expand into other countries in the region."<br>
 Curiel expects to sell 17 million CDMA phones this year in Korea, China and United States.<br>
<br>
 It's facilities in Incheon have the capacity to assemble 10 million units a year, 3.6million in-house and the remaining 6.4million outsourced through eight local manufactures.<br>
<br>
 This year, the company expects to produce 7.4 million phones, compared with 1.13million units in 2001.<br>
  "We are preparing to double the annual producing capacity next year to serve the fast-growing demand for CDMA-technology handsets." said J.J Lee, the executive director of Curitel responsible for manufacturing.<br>
<br>
 Founded in 1990, Pantech&Curitel began making CDMA handsets in 2000.<br>
It currently has a 10-15% share in Korea, behind Samsung and LG.<br>
<br>
[Bangkok Post September 18, 2003]<br>
</td>
              </tr>
